snippet.textDisplay:
READ IF THIS VIDEO DEMOTIVATED YOU


I don’t know who should hear this but here I go...

I remember being first year in university and watching LZ videos and think I wish I had as much as he does, but now I have changed my perspective.

I have just graduated my honours degree in accounting and I am a year older than Adam. I drive a 11 suzuki swift and live with my parents because I only start working next year. I do not live in a country where YouTube views are huge like in USA. So YouTube is not a lucrative business here. Therefore, studying and working while investing is my best option.

Moral of the story is: YOU ARE NOT A FAILURE. Everyone has their own journey and goal. Look at you own life and see Adam as motivation if you’d like and work towards it in your own way. You might not have over 16 cars at 25 but you may be the first person in your family with a car.

Just my 2 cents. Reach your goals. Remember it’s a marathon not a race.
